question_text:
Find the range of each of the following functions:
(i) f(x) = 2·3^x, where x ∈ ℝ and x > 0;
(ii) f(x) = x² + 2, where x is a real number;
(iii) f(x) = x, where x is a real number.

Example 19: Let R be a relation from ℚ to ℚ defined by R = {(a, b) : a, b ∈ ℚ and a - b ∈ ℤ}. Prove the following properties:
(i) (a, a) ∈ R for all a ∈ ℚ;
(ii) If (a, b) ∈ R then (b, a) ∈ R;
(iii) If (a, b) ∈ R and (b, c) ∈ R then (a, c) ∈ R.
